NAME:

    Iptables-Control - iptables filter configutrator

AUTHOR:
    
    'StealthP' Francesco <stealthp@stealthp.net>

DESCRIPTION:

    What is Iptables-Control?

    Iptables-Control is a fast and easy iptables filter configurator

    Some features:

     *Step-by-step interactive configurator script
     *TCP ports configurator
     *UDP ports configurator
     *LAN settings for routing and masquerading
     *ICMP filtering
    
   Tested on Red Hat 7.1 7.2 7.3 7.3 with kernel 2.4.19

FILES TREE:
   
   program: /sbin/iptables-control
   config file: /etc/iptables-control.conf
   Sample config : <package-dir>/sample-conf/iptables-control.conf.sample

   If you want remake a new configuration just remake a installation or
   go into <package-dir>/sbin/ and run genconf.sh as root

